<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFB1FFA0C6A4577FFD7DF853" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="208" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB1FFA2C6A4577FFBAFF8BA" blockId="5.[151,1437,1612,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB1FFA2C6A4577FFE9FF9C6" bold="true" box="[151,274,1612,1638]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Apical seta shorter than maximum width of palpus; setal palisade 1/2 length of mid tibia; setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half; tergite VI reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter with 3–4 setulae; sternite VI long, trapezoid, with 8–10 long setae on rear margin; dorsum of oviscape with 8–10 small setulae on each side, three of those near apex longer; venter of oviscape with 5 long setulae each side. Male. Setal palisade 2/3 length of mid tibia; fore tarsomere 5 longer than tarsomere 1; palpus apical seta less than 1.5 length of maximum width of palpus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB1FFA1C6F45617FF6BFF75" blockId="5.[151,1437,1612,2034]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,681]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="207" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB1FFA2C6F45617FE93F89E" bold="true" box="[199,286,1828,1854]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Female</emphasis>
. Frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB1FFA2C74D5617FE55F89E" box="[382,472,1828,1854]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-266@6.[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559536/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) brown, with 20–30 setulae. Supra-antennal setae as strong as adjacent frontal setae, lower pair being closer together and a little higher than lower fronto-orbital setae. Lower interfrontal seta near eye margin, but not directly under lower fronto-orbital seta. Lower fronto-orbital setae even nearer eye margin and a little lower on frons than upper supra-antennal setae. Second row of frontal setae almost straight, with upper interfrontal setae clearly further apart than either is from an upper fronto-orbital seta. Flagellomere 1 brown to pale brown and subglobose. Palpus whitish yellow, with short setae, apical one longer than adjacent setulae and shorter than maximum width of palpus. Labrum brown, small and triangular. Labella yellowish brown and tip of glossa brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB2FFA1C6FD51ECFEDDFE55" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
Thorax brown. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior twice length of anterior. Legs yellowish brown to brown, hind femora being darkest. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres about 0.61: 0.57: 0.58: 0.46: 1, with all five bearing a setal palisade (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB2FFA1C7D15014FDB1FEE1" box="[482,572,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-266@6.[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559536/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Setal palisade extends more than 1/2 length of mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB2FFA1C2E95014FAB8FEE1" box="[1242,1333,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-266@6.[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559536/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Setulae below basal half of hind femur longer than those of adjacent setulae of anterior face, but clearly shorter and weaker than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB2FFA1C4A7505CFD66FE29" box="[660,747,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-266@6.[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559536/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB2FFA1C579505CFC2DFE29" box="[842,928,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-266@6.[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559536/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB2FFA1C5CF505DFB2CFE29" box="[1020,1185,366,393]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.305" metricValueMax="1.36" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" unit="mm" value="1.305" valueMax="1.36" valueMin="1.25">1.25–1.36 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB2FFA1C2C0505DFA15FE29" box="[1267,1432,366,393]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" unit="mm" value="0.665" valueMax="0.68" valueMin="0.65">0.65–0.68 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.51. Costal index 0.40–0.42. Costal ratios 1.19–1.28: 1. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB2FFA1C26250A1FA9FFE0D" box="[1105,1298,402,429]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" metricValueMax="5.8999999999999995" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" unit="mm" value="0.055999999999999994" valueMax="0.059" valueMin="0.053">
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFB2FFA1C26250A1FB02FE0D" box="[1105,1167,402,429]" degrees="0.053" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" precision="55" value="0.053">0.053</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFB2FFA1C2BC50A1FB50FE0D" box="[1167,1245,402,429]" degrees="0.059" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" precision="55" value="-0.059">–0.059</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
long. Costa with 16–18 dorsal setulae. Alula with 2 setae. Veins brown, thin veins being paler. Membrane brownish gray. Haltere pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB2FFA1C6FD50CCFCD6FD09" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
Abdominal tergites brown and tergites 1–5 with sparse minute setulae only. Tergite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB2FFA1C28350CCFA9BFDB9" box="[1200,1302,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 24" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1388,188,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-19@33.[190,1398,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 24A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. quadrisetalis Liu et Cai; C–D. P. trapeziformis Zhang et Liu; E–F. P. inticlinatus sp. nov.; G–H. P. setipalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya; I–J. P. reticulatus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559613/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Fig. 24C</figureCitation>
) reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter bears 3–4 setulae at rear margin. Oviscape arched. The dorsum of the oviscape with about 8–10 small setulae each side, three of those near apex are a little longer (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB2FFA1C35C5374FF35FD25" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-266@6.[151,1435,702,1947]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559536/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
). The venter of the oviscape with 5 longer setulae each side. Venter brown. Sternite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB2FFA1C2B15358FB65FD25" box="[1154,1256,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 24" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[203,1388,188,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-19@33.[190,1398,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 24A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. quadrisetalis Liu et Cai; C–D. P. trapeziformis Zhang et Liu; E–F. P. inticlinatus sp. nov.; G–H. P. setipalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya; I–J. P. reticulatus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559613/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Fig. 24D</figureCitation>
) trapezoid, with 8–10 long setae on rear margin and some setulae on both sides.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6476E1FFB2FFA1C6A45685FAC3F852" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559536" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559536/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" startId="6.[151,264,1974,1998]" targetBox="[151,1435,702,1947]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB2FFA1C6A45685FAC3F852" blockId="6.[151,1436,1974,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB2FFA1C6A45685FEC1F86E" bold="true" box="[151,332,1974,1998]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">FIGURES 3A–F.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFB2FFA1C7605685FD66F86E" authority="Zhang et Liu" authorityName="Zhang et Liu" box="[339,747,1974,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trapeziformis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB2FFA1C7605685FDECF86E" box="[339,609,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Pseudacteon trapeziformis</emphasis>
Zhang 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB2FFA1C49E5684FD32F86E" box="[685,703,1975,1998]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">et</emphasis>
Liu
</taxonomicName>
, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB3FFA0C6F451A4FEFDFE29" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB3FFA0C6F451A4FE89FF11" bold="true" box="[199,260,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Male</emphasis>
. Frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB3FFA0C75451A4FE4FFF11" box="[359,450,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-130@7.[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. male terminalia, left view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) brown, with 14–20 setulae. Supra-antennal setae as strong as adjacent frontal setae, lower pair being closer together and a little higher than lower fronto-orbital setae. Lower interfrontal seta near eye margin, and directly under lower fronto-orbital seta. Lower fronto-orbital setae even nearer eye margin and a little lower on frons than upper supra-antennal setae. Second row of frontal setae concave, with upper interfrontal setae clearly further apart than either is from an upper fronto-orbital seta. Flagellomere 1 brown and subglobose. Palpus pale yellow, with long setae, apical one as long as or a little longer than maximum width of palpus. Labrum and labella pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6476E1FFB3FFA0C6A45718FAE7F9C7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559538" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" startId="7.[151,264,1579,1603]" targetBox="[151,1435,414,1553]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB3FFA0C6A45718FAE7F9C7" blockId="7.[151,1436,1579,1639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB3FFA0C6A45718FEC0F9E3" bold="true" box="[151,333,1579,1603]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">FIGURES 4A–F.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFB3FFA0C7665718FD7FF9E3" authority="Zhang et Liu" authorityName="Zhang et Liu" box="[341,754,1579,1603]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trapeziformis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB3FFA0C7665718FDE9F9E3" box="[341,612,1579,1603]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Pseudacteon trapeziformis</emphasis>
Zhang 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB3FFA0C480571FFD48F9E3" box="[691,709,1580,1603]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">et</emphasis>
Liu
</taxonomicName>
, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. male terminalia, left view. Scale bar = 0.1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB3FFA0C6F457A6FCFCF827" blockId="7.[151,1437,1685,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">
Thorax brown. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior twice length of anterior. Legs yellowish brown to brown, hind femora being darkest. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres about 0.94: 0.69: 0.69: 0.69: 1, with all five bearing a setal palisade (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB3FFA0C7D557EEFDCCF957" box="[486,577,1757,1783]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-130@7.[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. male terminalia, left view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Setal palisade extends more than 1/2 (0.60) length of mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB3FFA0C30757EEFA1DF957" box="[1332,1424,1757,1783]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-130@7.[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. male terminalia, left view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Setulae below basal half of hind femur clearly shorter and weaker than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB3FFA0C35C5632FF36F89F" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-130@7.[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. male terminalia, left view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB3FFA0C72A5616FEE2F89F" box="[281,367,1829,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-130@7.[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. male terminalia, left view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB3FFA0C7F95616FDE2F8E0" box="[458,623,1829,1856]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.29" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.28" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" unit="mm" value="1.29" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.28">1.28–1.30 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB3FFA0C4F25616FCE8F8E0" box="[705,869,1829,1856]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="6.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" unit="mm" value="0.665" valueMax="0.67" valueMin="0.66">0.66–0.67 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.52. Costal index 0.41–0.42. Costal ratios 1.33:1. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB3FFA0C789567AFDF4F8C4" box="[442,633,1865,1892]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6499999999999995" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" unit="mm" value="0.056499999999999995" valueMax="0.06" valueMin="0.053">
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFB3FFA0C789567AFE75F8C4" box="[442,504,1865,1892]" degrees="0.053" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" precision="55" value="0.053">0.053</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFB3FFA0C7CB567AFDCBF8C4" box="[504,582,1865,1892]" degrees="0.060" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" precision="55" value="-0.06">–0.060</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
long. Costa with 16 dorsal setulae. Alula with 2 setae. Veins brown, thin veins being paler. Membrane brownish gray. Haltere pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB3FFA0C6FC56A2FD7DF853" blockId="7.[151,1437,1685,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">
Abdominal tergites brown and tergites 1–6 with sparse minute setulae only. Venter brown. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB3FFA0C6935686FF7FF86F" box="[160,242,1973,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-130@7.[151,1435,414,1553]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 4A–F. Pseudacteon trapeziformis Zhang et Liu, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, anterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. male terminalia, left view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559538/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
) brown, anal tube pale yellow. Left side of epandrium slender and tapered, with some setulae at apex. Right side of epandrium a little broad, with setulae apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
