<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFBCFFAFC6F45079FEAFFDC0" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFBCFFAFC6F45079FEAFFDC0" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC6F45079FEB9FEC4" bold="true" box="[199,308,330,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is easily recognized from other species in having a trapezoid sternite VI and a row of 8–10 setulae on its rear margin. In the key to Russian Far East (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFBCFFAFC568505DFB55FE28" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[859,1240,366,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref22089" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V. (2000) New species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from the Far East of Russia. Fragmenta Faunistica, 43 (4), 35 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2000.43.4.035" type="journal article" year="2000">Disney and Michailovskaya 2000</bibRefCitation>
), the species runs to couplets 4 to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFBCFFAFC77C50A0FCE8FE0C" authority="Disney et Michailovskaya, 2000" authorityName="Disney et Michailovskaya" authorityYear="2000" box="[335,869,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rudisetosus">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC77C50A0FE61FE0C" box="[335,492,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">P. rudisetosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFBCFFAFC7C750A1FCE8FE0C" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[500,869,402,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref22089" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V. (2000) New species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from the Far East of Russia. Fragmenta Faunistica, 43 (4), 35 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2000.43.4.035" type="journal article" year="2000">
Disney 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC47850A0FDD2FE0C" box="[587,607,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">et</emphasis>
Michailovskaya, 2000
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it is immediately distinguished from the latter by the shape of sternite VI and its chaetotaxy. In the key to European species (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFBCFFAFC5E75085FBEAFE70" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Withers, P." box="[980,1127,438,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref22148" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Withers, P. (2009) A new species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) and a new key to the European species. Fragmenta Faunistica, 52 (1), 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2009.52.1.001" type="journal article" year="2009">Disney 2009</bibRefCitation>
), the new species runs up to couplet 4 to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFBCFFAFC71050E8FDE5FE55" authority="Schmitz, 1925" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1925" box="[291,616,474,501]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC71050E8FE31FE54" box="[291,444,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">P. brevicauda</emphasis>
Schmitz, 1925
</taxonomicName>
, it differs from the latter by shorter and thicker setae of palpus and shape of sternite VI. The male of the species is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFBCFFAFC52D50CCFABEFDB8" authority="Disney et Michailovskaya, 2000" authorityName="Disney et Michailovskaya" authorityYear="2000" box="[798,1331,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setipalpatus">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC52D50CCFC4DFDB8" box="[798,960,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">P. setipalpatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFBCFFAFC5F450CDFABEFDB8" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[967,1331,510,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref22089" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V. (2000) New species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from the Far East of Russia. Fragmenta Faunistica, 43 (4), 35 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2000.43.4.035" type="journal article" year="2000">
Disney 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC22E50CCFBBCFDB8" box="[1053,1073,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">et</emphasis>
Michailovskaya, 2000
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs from the latter by apical seta less than two times of the maximum width of palpus and fore tarsomere 5 longer than tarsomere 1.
</paragraph>
